  <h2>We Handle the Complications</h2>
  <p>Whether the home is in pristine condition or hasn't been touched in years, we buy as-is. We can work with your attorney or title company to navigate probate, and we're flexible on timing if the estate needs time to settle.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Buy directly from the estate or heirs</li>
    <li>Work alongside probate attorneys</li>
    <li>Purchase in any condition — full of belongings is fine</li>
    <li>No commissions or closing costs</li>
    <li>Flexible timeline to accommodate the estate process</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Honest Trade-Off</h2>
  <p>A cash offer will typically be below full retail market value — that's the trade-off for speed, certainty, and zero prep costs. But when you factor in commissions (5–6%), repair costs, carrying costs during a 60–90 day listing, and the risk of deals falling through — a fair cash offer often puts more money in your pocket than you'd expect.</p>
  <p>We'll always give you a straight answer. If the traditional route is actually better for your situation, we'll tell you that.</p>

